# Macro Monitor Skill

When the user asks for macro data, GDP/CPI/PPI/PMI/social financing/M2/rates/FX, industry prosperity, high-frequency macro signals, economic calendars, macro weekly/monthly reports, or macro monitoring, use the local skill package.

Preferred local project path:

```text
.cursor/skills/macro-monitor
```

Workflow:

1. Read `.cursor/skills/macro-monitor/SKILL.md`.
2. For reports, industry work, calendar tracking, or monitoring specs, also read `.cursor/skills/macro-monitor/references/macro-monitor-guide.md`.
3. Use the Pandadata API skill for exact method contracts. If available in the same project, read `.cursor/skills/pandadata-api/SKILL.md` and inspect method docs before calling APIs.
4. Start with `get_macro_detail` to confirm indicator codes; do not invent codes, fields, units, or release dates.
5. Include method, parameters, latest period, unit, and stale-data notes for every material macro claim.
